Wacom’s Feel IT Technologies Sharpen The Edge Of Samsung’s Innovation In GALAXY Note



十月 28th, 2011
 | Categories: Latest News



Wacom is delighted to announce its partnership with  Samsung’s Mobile  Communications Business in providing  digital pen interface technology for their premium product GALAXY  Note.
This is the first  smart phone that brings Wacom’s world leading digital pen technology to  portable mobile  devices giving users greater freedom, precision and creativity.
Users can now use both simple and direct touch navigation with  precise and flexible pen input for a wide range of applications such as taking  memos, sketching ideas, editing photos or personalizing communications including  emails, tweets, blogs and posts.
“Our mission  is to provide the best user interface experiences that are creative, natural,  precise and intuitive to use. Our partnership with Samsung is an important step  for us to introduce a new way of user interaction, enabling people to enjoy  their own creativity. From now on, technology will feel different.” says  Masahiko Yamada, President & CEO of Wacom Co., Ltd.
Wacom’s  feel IT technologies include high precision digital pens, multi-touch sensors,  controllers and device drivers, which can all be integrated into a wide range of  mobile systems to provide natural, intuitive user experiences.
About Wacom
Wacom’s vision to bring people and technology closer together through  natural interface technologies has made it the world’s leading manufacturer of  pen tablets, interactive pen displays and digital interface solutions. The  advanced technology of Wacom’s intuitive input devices has been used to create  some of the most exciting digital art, films, special effects, fashions and  designs around the world.  Wacom devices provide business and home users with  the ability to explore digital content creation in a comfortable, natural way.
 


