Orange Business Services will deploy unified communications services for Gemalto using Microsoft Lync



十月 27th, 2011
 | Categories: Latest News



Orange Business Services announces the signing of a contract with Gemalto, a world  leader in digital security, for the deployment of unified  communications and collaboration services using the Microsoft Lync solution  (instant messaging, unified messaging, presence, audio and Web conferencing and  VoIP services). Currently in the pilot phase, this global project will  eventually include all Gemalto employees, approximately 10,000 people across 148  sites in 45 countries.
In signing this contract, Orange  Business Services confirms its expertise in Microsoft solution integration and  demonstrates its ambition in the Voice and Unified Communications sector with  Microsoft in both the French and international markets.
By deploying Business  Together with Microsoft Lync, Gemalto seeks to facilitate  collaboration between its staff across the various subsidiaries of the group and  also to reduce the cost of internal communications and Web conferencing. With  the centralized approach chosen by the Gemalto IT department, all subsidiaries  of the group will be able to benefit from a reduced Total Cost of Ownership and  optimization of telephony costs thanks to Least Cost Routing.
Cédric Parent, Marketing Director of  Unified Communication & Collaboration, Orange Business Services, said:   “We are very happy with the  confidence that Gemalto has shown in us to carry out this project. Gemalto was  looking for a stakeholder capable of providing comprehensive expertise for the  Microsoft Lync solution and who could guarantee a global deployment. This  project represents a major step forward in our strategy of being the No.1  Microsoft telephony company in France.”
Expertise in  Microsoft solution integration
The performance of Orange Business  Services was rewarded at the Microsoft Worldwide Partner Conference held last  July in Los  Angeles. The operator and integrator was awarded the  “Partner of the Year 2011 France”  prize in recognition of the commercial success of its products using BPOS and Office  365. Orange Business Services currently has more than 1,000 customers,  increasing its position as the principal global partner for Office 365. Thanks  to the center of expertise provided by its subsidiary Alsy, the specialist  Microsoft solutions integrator that was acquired in 2010, Orange Business  Services is also “Voice Partner of the Year  France” as a  result of deploying the vast majority of the telephony contracts which use  Microsoft technology in France. On its team, Alsy has one of  the few Microsoft Certified Masters for Lync in France who is also the youngest  ever.
 
 
About Orange Business Services
Orange Business  Services, the France Telecom-Orange branch dedicated to B2B services, is a  leading global integrator of communications solutions for multinational  corporations. With the world’s  largest, seamless network for voice and data, Orange Business Services reaches  220 countries and territories with local support in 166. Offering a  comprehensive package of communication services covering cloud computing,  enterprise mobility, M2M, security, unified communications, videoconferencing,  and broadband, Orange Business Services delivers a best-in-class customer  experience across a global landscape. Thousands of enterprise customers and 1.4  million mobile data users rely on an Orange Business Services international  platform for communicating and conducting business. Orange Business Services is  a four-time winner of Best Global Operator at the World Communication Awards.  Learn more at www.orange-business.com
France  Telecom-Orange is one of the world’s leading telecommunications operators with  170,000 employees worldwide and sales of 22.6 billion euros in the first  semester 2011. Orange is the Group’s single brand for Internet, television and mobile  services in the majority of countries where the company operates. France Telecom  (NYSE:FTE) is listed on Euronext Paris (compartment A) and on the New York Stock  Exchange.
 


